pages.title: Blue Catfish
pages.text: The blue catfish ($(o)Ictalurus furcatus$()) is the largest species of North American catfish, reaching a length of 165 cm ($(o)65 in$()) and a weight of 68 kg ($(o)150 lb).$(br2)The typical length is about 25–46 in ($(o)64–117 cm).$(br2)The fish can live to 20 years.
